<div class="intro-pull"><strong>The Uintah Basin runs on workers who need a reliable place to stay.</strong> Best Western Vernal Inn is built for exactly that — weekly and monthly rates that fit per diem budgets, kitchenettes so crews can cook instead of eating out every meal, free hot breakfast every morning before shift, and a location just 0.6 miles from Vernal Regional Airport for easy crew rotations. We've hosted oilfield teams, pipeline contractors, BLM surveyors, and utility crews for years. The rooms are clean, the rates are fair, and the front desk knows how shift work operates.</div>
<div class="content-section">
 <h2>Why Crews Choose Best Western Vernal Inn</h2>
<p>Workforce housing in Vernal usually means one of two options: a bare-bones motel with no kitchen and no breakfast, or an overpriced chain that doesn't understand per diem budgets. Best Western Vernal Inn sits in the middle — full-service rooms with kitchenettes, free hot breakfast, and weekly rates starting at $588 that align with GSA per diem guidelines for Uintah County. We're 0.6 miles from the airport for crew rotations, and we have the parking to handle work trucks, trailers, and company vehicles.</p>
